9,"flags":0,"comment_count":1,"description":"","description_plain":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/moe2iz/put_pin_on","submitter_user":{"username":"markhollis","created_at":"2017-09-25T01:23:41.000-05:00","is_admin":false,"about":"","is_moderator":false,"karma":18,"avatar_url":"/avatars/markhollis-100.png","invited_by_user":"singpolyma"},"tags":["rust"]},{"short_id":"tbi01x","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/tbi01x","created_at":"2023-07-14T14:52:30.000-05:00","title":"Framework laptop or Macbook?","url":"","score":25,"flags":2,"comment_count":74,"description":"\u003cp\u003eI’m in the market for a new laptop.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI’ve narrowed it down to a Framework Laptop 13 with a Ryzen processor, or a flavor of Macbook.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI’ve unfortunately become trained to only want to use a tiling window manager like i3. Obviously I can slap Linux on the Framework directly, but with the Macbook I’d probably be running Linux in a VM most of the time. The reason the Macbook is in the running at all is because of the hardware quality and the sheer oomph of the M2.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Framework appeal is the sheer consumer-friendliness of the thing. I’d like to support that.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWould love any thoughts!\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEdit: thank everyone so much for all the replies, I read all of them and really appreciate it. I think it’ll come down to how Asahi Linux is doing. I’ll do my research and make a pick. Thank you all once again, Lobsters are awesome :)\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"I'm in the market for a new laptop.\r\n\r\nI've narrowed it down to a Framework Laptop 13 with a Ryzen processor, or a flavor of Macbook. \r\n\r\nI've unfortunately become trained to only want to use a tiling window manager like i3. Obviously I can slap Linux on the Framework directly, but with the Macbook I'd probably be running Linux in a VM most of the time. The reason the Macbook is in the running at all is because of the hardware quality and the sheer oomph of the M2.\r\n\r\nThe Framework appeal is the sheer consumer-friendliness of the thing. I'd like to support that.\r\n\r\nWould love any thoughts!\r\n\r\nEdit: thank everyone so much for all the replies, I read all of them and really appreciate it. I think it’ll come down to how Asahi Linux is doing. I’ll do my research and make a pick. Thank you all once again, Lobsters are awesome :)","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/tbi01x/framework_laptop_macbook","submitter_user":{"username":"cflewis","created_at":"2016-12-15T11:47:56.000-06:00","is_admin":false,"about":"Google employee. Of course, everything I say is my own opinion, and does not necessarily reflect the opinions of my employer.\r\n\r\nI no longer work on the Go team.\r\n\r\nI finished my PhD at UC Santa Cruz.\r\n\r\nhttp://www.cflewis.com","is_moderator":false,"karma":780,"avatar_url":"/avatars/cflewis-100.png","invited_by_user":"munificent"},"tags":["ask","hardware"]}]